cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about image captioning, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses attention mechanisms and reinforcement learning, which are common in natural language processing, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for image captioning, which involves multiple components and learning techniques, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with generating captions from images, which involves information retrieval and search, suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely but still possible category.
